cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Layer 2 Network Latency and Energy Consumption Measurements under Variable
  Packet Rates and Sizes in System-Level Experiment
abstract: This dataset captures latency and energy consumption metrics from Layer
  2 forwarding workloads executed on two nodes under varying packet rates and sizes.
  The experiment uses a Lua-based forwarding application and Moongen load generator
  to synchronize traffic generation, measurement periods, and remote port configuration.
  It evaluates performance through controlled traffic scenarios, logging process outputs,
  energy metrics, and post-test visualizations. The collection includes setup scripts,
  per-run logs, and evaluation artifacts for analyzing deterministic execution conditions
  and network stress responses.
